00:18:42,400 --> 00:18:43,640
He kept telling us

557
00:18:43,640 --> 00:18:45,480
not to bother him at 6AM.

558
00:18:45,480 --> 00:18:46,160
So maybe

559
00:18:46,160 --> 00:18:47,360
he died here at 6AM.

560
00:18:47,640 --> 00:18:48,040
Wait.

561
00:18:48,040 --> 00:18:49,520
Let's go over the timeline.

562
00:18:49,520 --> 00:18:51,320
The cafe opens

563
00:18:51,320 --> 00:18:52,360
at 10AM, right?

564
00:18:52,460 --> 00:18:53,200
(Timeline: 10AM, cafe day shift opens)

565
00:18:53,200 --> 00:18:55,720
Then from 10 to

566
00:18:55,720 --> 00:18:56,160
7PM,

567
00:18:56,160 --> 00:18:58,520
we sell coffee.

568
00:18:58,520 --> 00:19:00,520
(10AM to 7PM, daytime cafe.
7PM, day shift ends)

569
00:19:00,560 --> 00:19:02,560
Then work starts again at midnight,

570
00:19:02,560 --> 00:19:03,960
(12AM, cafe night shift opens)
and until 4AM, we sell alcohol.

571
00:19:03,960 --> 00:19:04,280
(7PM to 12AM, closed)
Alcohol.

572
00:19:04,280 --> 00:19:04,600
Alcohol.

573
00:19:04,600 --> 00:19:05,720
(4AM, night shift ends)
Right. The alcohol shift.

574
00:19:05,720 --> 00:19:07,080
(12 to 4AM., night drinks)
From 4 to 10AM,

575
00:19:07,080 --> 00:19:07,960
(10AM, day shift opens)
we're closed.

576
00:19:08,360 --> 00:19:10,320
(4 to 10AM, closed)
The manager comes in at 6AM.

577
00:19:10,320 --> 00:19:11,760
(6AM, Manager Tui works out)
He told us not to come in.

578
00:19:11,760 --> 00:19:12,040
Right.

579
00:19:12,040 --> 00:19:13,080
We definitely wouldn't come in then.

580
00:19:13,080 --> 00:19:14,200
At 6AM, we'd be asleep.

581
00:19:14,200 --> 00:19:14,480
Right.

582
00:19:14,480 --> 00:19:16,080
So his time of death

583
00:19:16,080 --> 00:19:18,440
was probably between 6 and 10AM

584
00:19:18,500 --> 00:19:18,970
(Current case summary)

585
00:19:18,970 --> 00:19:19,470
(Victim: Manager Tui)

586
00:19:19,470 --> 00:19:20,460
(Scene: Starlight Cafe VIP room)

587
00:19:20,480 --> 00:19:21,540
(Estimated time of death: 6 to 10AM)

588
00:19:21,560 --> 00:19:23,080
(No room to stand)
Can we move the body out first?

589
00:19:23,720 --> 00:19:24,160
Come on.

590
00:19:24,480 --> 00:19:24,920
Careful.

591
00:19:26,020 --> 00:19:27,020
(All hands on deck)

592
00:19:27,480 --> 00:19:28,560
He's so heavy.

593
00:19:28,560 --> 00:19:29,080
Put him here.

594
00:19:29,080 --> 00:19:30,040
Here, in the lobby.

595
00:19:30,040 --> 00:19:31,040
Three, two, one, go.

596
00:19:32,040 --> 00:19:33,040
His face!

597
00:19:35,520 --> 00:19:35,960
Okay.

598
00:19:35,960 --> 00:19:37,160
If you weren't the detective,

599
00:19:37,160 --> 00:19:37,960
(Very suspicious behavior)

600
00:19:37,960 --> 00:19:39,320
I'd arrest you.

601
00:19:41,600 --> 00:19:42,440
No, it's at the front.

602
00:19:42,440 --> 00:19:43,160
The front.

603
00:19:43,160 --> 00:19:43,480
The hat.

604
00:19:43,480 --> 00:19:43,760
Come here.

605
00:19:44,720 --> 00:19:45,760
Okay.

606
00:19:45,900 --> 00:19:47,740
(If you're stressed, come look at me)

607
00:19:47,760 --> 00:19:48,960
Why is there blood?

608
00:19:49,680 --> 00:19:50,440
There's blood?

609
00:19:50,440 --> 00:19:51,640
(Got blood on him)

610
00:19:51,640 --> 00:19:52,880
Where did you touch blood?

611
00:19:52,880 --> 00:19:53,840
I don't know.

612
00:19:56,840 --> 00:19:58,160
Here. Right here.

613
00:19:59,420 --> 00:20:00,500
(Head wound)

614
00:20:00,520 --> 00:20:01,400
His head!

615
00:20:01,400 --> 00:20:02,320
It's split open.

616
00:20:02,320 --> 00:20:03,800
He was hit.

617
00:20:03,800 --> 00:20:05,320
Probably with a blunt object.

618
00:20:06,320 --> 00:20:09,280
So this could be the fatal wound.

619
00:20:09,280 --> 00:20:09,620
Right.

620
00:20:09,700 --> 00:20:11,660
(Possible cause of death: hit or struck
with a blunt object)

621
00:20:12,360 --> 00:20:13,080
What's this?

622
00:20:13,080 --> 00:20:13,920
There's a ring on his hand.

623
00:20:13,920 --> 00:20:14,480
Take it off.

624
00:20:14,700 --> 00:20:16,380
(Tassel ring)

625
00:20:19,800 --> 00:20:21,800
This ring suddenly makes me

626
00:20:21,800 --> 00:20:23,400
suspect a certain woman.

627
00:20:24,360 --> 00:20:26,040
Looks like a love token.

628
00:20:26,720 --> 00:20:28,680
My fingers are too thin. It doesn't fit.

629
00:20:28,680 --> 00:20:29,920
No, it's adjustable.

630
00:20:29,920 --> 00:20:31,080
You know a lot about it.

631
00:20:31,500 --> 00:20:32,820
(Walked right into that)

632
00:20:33,020 --> 00:20:35,500
(Uh-oh)

633
00:20:35,520 --> 00:20:37,840
He has a little tassel on his hand.

634
00:20:37,840 --> 00:20:39,680
Maybe it points to someone
with a big one here.

635
00:20:39,680 --> 00:20:40,680
It's not me. I swear!

636
00:20:40,680 --> 00:20:41,300
It isn't me!

637
00:20:41,300 --> 00:20:42,260
(Please spare me)

638
00:20:42,420 --> 00:20:44,020
(What does the tassel ring point to?)

639
00:20:44,040 --> 00:20:44,920
Wait.

640
00:20:44,920 --> 00:20:45,440
It says here.

641
00:20:45,440 --> 00:20:46,960
When everyone is inside the cafe,

642
00:20:46,960 --> 00:20:50,600
if someone presses the backup
door button for the VIP room,

643
00:20:50,600 --> 00:20:52,280
this sensor light will turn on.

644
00:20:53,440 --> 00:20:54,040
For example,

645
00:20:54,040 --> 00:20:54,640
you.

646
00:20:54,640 --> 00:20:55,920
You wouldn't need it,

647
00:20:55,920 --> 00:20:56,680
because you have a card.

648
00:20:56,680 --> 00:20:57,040
Right.

649
00:20:57,040 --> 00:20:57,440
You have a card.

650
00:20:57,440 --> 00:20:59,080
So the backup light wouldn't
come on. Right?

651
00:20:59,080 --> 00:20:59,600
Right.

652
00:20:59,600 --> 00:21:01,440
(Other than Gold Card holders,
others may also enter the VIP area)

653
00:21:01,440 --> 00:21:03,000
Let's check that phone, okay?

654
00:21:03,000 --> 00:21:05,880
(The phone fell from the body)
And there's a camera-like thing.

655
00:21:05,880 --> 00:21:08,040
(Timed camera)
It recorded his whole death.

656
00:21:09,660 --> 00:21:11,700
(The timed camera recorded
the killer's crime)

657
00:21:11,720 --> 00:21:12,600
It says down here,

658
00:21:12,600 --> 00:21:14,000
timed camera.

659
00:21:14,000 --> 00:21:15,400
You can set the recording length.

660
00:21:15,400 --> 00:21:16,360
After recording,

661
00:21:16,360 --> 00:21:17,480
(Timed camera)
if the video isn't deleted

662
00:21:17,480 --> 00:21:18,480
within one minute,

663
00:21:18,480 --> 00:21:21,520
it'll auto-upload to the linked
social media account.

664
00:21:24,600 --> 00:21:25,240
Here's one...

665
00:21:25,240 --> 00:21:26,120
We can scan it.

666
00:21:26,640 --> 00:21:28,880
Scan to view the latest saved video.

667
00:21:28,880 --> 00:21:29,280
Okay.

668
00:21:29,280 --> 00:21:30,000
Scan it.

669
00:21:30,000 --> 00:21:31,440
Let's see who it really is.

670
00:21:32,040 --> 00:21:34,680
Don't let me catch even one tiny clue.

671
00:21:34,680 --> 00:21:36,060
Or I'll beat you up!

672
00:21:36,060 --> 00:21:36,860
(The detective
is getting a bit intense)

673
00:21:39,940 --> 00:21:41,020
(Manager Tui's workout video)

674
00:21:42,480 --> 00:21:42,840
Wait.

675
00:21:42,840 --> 00:21:44,240
Let's see the killer's face.

676
00:21:46,600 --> 00:21:48,320
Timed recording, 30 seconds.

677
00:21:48,320 --> 00:21:49,360
He's doing push-ups.

678
00:21:49,360 --> 00:21:50,860
(Timed recording, 30 seconds)

679
00:21:51,980 --> 00:21:53,140
(Voice-over in progress)

680
00:21:53,160 --> 00:21:54,760
Is this just a workout?

681
00:21:55,760 --> 00:21:56,320
Push-ups.

682
00:21:56,320 --> 00:21:57,100
He looks like he's about to give up.

683
00:21:57,260 --> 00:21:58,380
(Someone attacks Manager Tui
from behind)

684
00:21:59,520 --> 00:22:00,240
A hammer.

685
00:22:00,240 --> 00:22:03,340
Preliminarily, that
could be the fatal weapon.

686
00:22:03,420 --> 00:22:03,670
(Current case summary:
Victim, Manager Tui)

687
00:22:03,670 --> 00:22:03,960
(Death location:
Starlight Cafe VIP room)

688
00:22:03,960 --> 00:22:04,420
(Estimated time of death: 6 to 10AM)

689
00:22:04,420 --> 00:22:04,810
(Cause of death: Blunt-force trauma
to the head with a hammer)

690
00:22:04,840 --> 00:22:05,160
Wait.

691
00:22:05,160 --> 00:22:05,720
The hand.

692
00:22:05,960 --> 00:22:06,640
Look at the hand.

693
00:22:06,640 --> 00:22:07,840
Is that a man's or a woman's hand?

694
00:22:08,020 --> 00:22:09,300
(Instantly locked on)

695
00:22:09,320 --> 00:22:10,240
That thumb

696
00:22:10,240 --> 00:22:11,840
looks kind of unusual.

697
00:22:11,840 --> 00:22:12,680
The height too...

698
00:22:12,680 --> 00:22:13,720
I think it really looks like his.

699
00:22:14,160 --> 00:22:14,760
It looks like you!

700
00:22:14,760 --> 00:22:16,000
It's yours!

701
00:22:16,000 --> 00:22:17,520
(Manually shortened)
My thumb is too short!

702
00:22:17,520 --> 00:22:19,160
My finger is only this long.

703
00:22:19,160 --> 00:22:20,480
(Not me either)
That's just how mine is.

704
00:22:20,760 --> 00:22:21,580
I don't have a thumb.

705
00:22:21,620 --> 00:22:23,260
(To clear his name,
he's willing to lose a finger)

706
00:22:23,280 --> 00:22:24,080
You don't have a thumb?

707
00:22:24,080 --> 00:22:24,740
(You're the real savage)

708
00:22:25,520 --> 00:22:26,000
Alright.

709
00:22:26,560 --> 00:22:27,360
Let's check the phone.

710
00:22:28,400 --> 00:22:28,880
Manager Tui.

711
00:22:28,880 --> 00:22:29,540
(Manager Tui's phone)

712
00:22:32,440 --> 00:22:32,900
Wait.

713
00:22:32,900 --> 00:22:33,620
(Missed call)

714
00:22:33,960 --> 00:22:37,640
Liu Lian Wangfan called him and missed.

715
00:22:38,160 --> 00:22:40,160
That's the ringtone we just heard.

716
00:22:40,160 --> 00:22:40,680
Exactly.

717
00:22:40,740 --> 00:22:41,840
(The person who just
called was Liu Lian Wangfan)

718
00:22:41,840 --> 00:22:43,400
Are there other clues on the phone?

719
00:22:44,800 --> 00:22:46,480
Liu Lian Wangfan's texts.

720
00:22:47,160 --> 00:22:48,690
January 1, 2026.

721
00:22:48,800 --> 00:22:49,640
Liu Lian Wangfan said,

722
00:22:49,640 --> 00:22:50,680
"Happy New Year, Manager Tui."

723
00:22:50,680 --> 00:22:52,400
"I heard your shop hired a few more"

724
00:22:52,400 --> 00:22:53,720
"low-class employees."

725
00:22:54,440 --> 00:22:55,440
(That felt personal)
What does that mean?

726
00:22:55,440 --> 00:22:56,600
This Liu Lian Wangfan...

727
00:22:57,160 --> 00:22:58,280
Low-class?

728
00:22:58,280 --> 00:22:59,360
We're all stage people!

729
00:22:59,360 --> 00:23:00,240
(We're basically the pillars
of the stage)

730
00:23:00,240 --> 00:23:01,920
What kind of stage
is that hard to get on?

731
00:23:03,400 --> 00:23:04,280
On March 1, he said,

732
00:23:04,280 --> 00:23:05,200
"Are you even human?"

733
00:23:05,200 --> 00:23:07,240
"You poached my people,
and you're acting so righteous?"

734
00:23:07,240 --> 00:23:09,400
He's crashing out more every day.

735
00:23:09,400 --> 00:23:10,220
(Tough words are just
your defense mechanism)

736
00:23:11,120 --> 00:23:11,680
April 5.

737
00:23:12,120 --> 00:23:13,800
"No wonder you don't
let employees into your office."

738
00:23:13,800 --> 00:23:15,480
"You must be doing
something shady in there."

739
00:23:15,480 --> 00:23:16,560
"Aren't you afraid of karma?"

740
00:23:17,260 --> 00:23:19,620
(Why didn't Manager Tui
let employees into his office?)

741
00:23:19,640 --> 00:23:21,080
Something shady?

742
00:23:21,080 --> 00:23:22,120
So we can conclude

743
00:23:22,120 --> 00:23:23,200
Liu Lian Wangfan

744
00:23:23,200 --> 00:23:24,040
is all bark.

745
00:23:24,400 --> 00:23:25,400
(Keyboard warrior)
He's been making threats

746
00:23:25,400 --> 00:23:26,400
for over three months.

747
00:23:26,400 --> 00:23:27,280
And he might be

748
00:23:27,280 --> 00:23:28,840
the owner of another cafe.

749
00:23:28,840 --> 00:23:29,080
Yes.

750
00:23:29,080 --> 00:23:29,440
Right.

751
00:23:29,440 --> 00:23:31,040
So they're competitors.

752
00:23:31,100 --> 00:23:32,820
(Liu Lian Wangfan owns a rival cafe)

753
00:23:32,840 --> 00:23:33,980
I've been to that shop.

754
00:23:33,980 --> 00:23:35,020
(Jin used to be
Liu Lian Wangfan's customer)

755
00:23:35,280 --> 00:23:35,680
Really?

756
00:23:37,360 --> 00:23:38,360
Any random guy there

757
00:23:38,360 --> 00:23:39,520
is better than them?

758
00:23:43,520 --> 00:23:44,960
No. That place isn't good.

759
00:23:44,960 --> 00:23:45,440
Okay.

760
00:23:45,440 --> 00:23:46,440
(Only real customers tell the truth)
It's nowhere near this place.

761
00:23:46,440 --> 00:23:46,840
So I...

762
00:23:46,840 --> 00:23:48,100
Did you get a Gold Card there too?

763
00:23:48,100 --> 00:23:48,980
(Getting straight to the point)

764
00:23:51,840 --> 00:23:53,440
Did you also find someone else there?

765
00:23:53,440 --> 00:23:54,760
How many Gold Cards do you have?

766
00:23:54,760 --> 00:23:56,020
Who did you buy Gold Cards for?

767
00:23:56,020 --> 00:23:56,780
(So how many cards does Jin have?)

768
00:23:56,900 --> 00:23:57,740
(Innocent)

769
00:23:57,760 --> 00:23:58,240
Who did you open cards for?

770
00:23:58,240 --> 00:23:59,960
How many cards do you have?

771
00:24:00,100 --> 00:24:01,500
(Why are you quiet again
when it's hard to answer?)

772
00:24:01,920 --> 00:24:02,680
Is it...

773
00:24:03,280 --> 00:24:05,620
Is it wrong to like beautiful things?

774
00:24:05,620 --> 00:24:06,740
(Fair enough)

775
00:24:08,080 --> 00:24:08,620
Okay.

776
00:24:08,620 --> 00:24:10,220
(We'll let you off)

777
00:24:11,480 --> 00:24:13,640
Liu Lian Wangfan sent another message.

778
00:24:13,640 --> 00:24:15,380
(You'll pay with your life)
You'll pay with your life.

779
00:24:15,380 --> 00:24:16,820
(Liu Lian Wangfan sends another message)

780
00:24:16,840 --> 00:24:17,560
"I'm coming for you."

781
00:24:17,560 --> 00:24:18,200
"Come out."

782
00:24:18,960 --> 00:24:19,760
What a dummy.

783
00:24:19,760 --> 00:24:20,840
He's already dead.

784
00:24:21,280 --> 00:24:21,800
"Just you wait."

785
00:24:21,800 --> 00:24:22,680
"I'm coming for you now."

786
00:24:22,680 --> 00:24:23,320
"Come out."

787
00:24:23,320 --> 00:24:24,400
That means he's almost here.

788
00:24:24,400 --> 00:24:25,240
Let's wait outside.

789
00:24:25,240 --> 00:24:26,480
We'll wait for him.

790
00:24:26,480 --> 00:24:27,000
He said

791
00:24:27,000 --> 00:24:28,960
we're not good enough.

792
00:24:28,960 --> 00:24:30,440
(How dare he mess with us?)
Let's see what's going on.

793
00:24:30,440 --> 00:24:31,520
Let's see what's going on.

794
00:24:32,440 --> 00:24:33,880
I'm closing the door.

795
00:24:37,280 --> 00:24:37,920
He really came.

796
00:24:37,920 --> 00:24:38,560
Hey, handsome.

797
00:24:39,160 --> 00:24:40,240
Get Manager Tui out here!

798
00:24:40,240 --> 00:24:40,780
(He's not here to be friendly)

799
00:24:41,120 --> 00:24:43,000
(Gym bro Zhou Hao, played by Lin Bin)
Where is he? Get him out here!

800
00:24:43,540 --> 00:24:44,220
(We can only carry him out)

801
00:24:44,240 --> 00:24:44,880
Our manager...

802
00:24:44,880 --> 00:24:47,920
Step back.

803
00:24:47,920 --> 00:24:49,120
I'm about to...

804
00:24:49,120 --> 00:24:50,010
(Go on. Do your thing)
Step back.

805
00:24:50,080 --> 00:24:50,840
Squat down!

806
00:24:52,160 --> 00:24:52,680
What?

807
00:24:52,680 --> 00:24:53,480
Uh...

808
00:24:53,480 --> 00:24:54,440
You may rise.

809
00:24:54,440 --> 00:24:55,760
He's here.

810
00:24:55,760 --> 00:24:56,600
Liu Lian Wangfan is here.

811
00:25:05,520 --> 00:25:06,000
Sir,

812
00:25:06,000 --> 00:25:06,800
what's going on?

813
00:25:06,800 --> 00:25:07,380
Listen up.

814
00:25:07,420 --> 00:25:08,820
(Behind-the-Scenes Interviews
at 12PM every Fri)

815
00:25:08,840 --> 00:25:10,740
(See more fun behind-the-scenes moments)
My name is Liu Lian Wangfan.

816
00:25:10,740 --> 00:25:11,660
(Liu Lian Wangfan,
played by Liu Xiaoting)

817
00:25:11,960 --> 00:25:13,120
That's him.

818
00:25:13,120 --> 00:25:14,800
I'm here to settle a score today!

819
00:25:16,760 --> 00:25:17,920
Who are you settling scores with?

820
00:25:18,560 --> 00:25:20,040
Jin Cardashian.

821
00:25:22,120 --> 00:25:24,560
With me? No way!

822
00:25:24,560 --> 00:25:26,800
You didn't come home for seven days.

823
00:25:26,860 --> 00:25:27,760
(The gossip is heating up)

824
00:25:27,760 --> 00:25:28,520
What's your relationship?

825
00:25:29,000 --> 00:25:30,800
So you really are here.

826
00:25:31,580 --> 00:25:32,500
(You have another home?)

827
00:25:32,520 --> 00:25:33,280
Wait. Home?

828
00:25:33,280 --> 00:25:34,680
Are you two family?

829
00:25:34,680 --> 00:25:35,720
Which home

830
00:25:35,720 --> 00:25:37,160
are you talking about?

831
00:25:38,600 --> 00:25:39,640
Who's that...

832
00:25:39,640 --> 00:25:41,280
He something?

833
00:25:41,280 --> 00:25:42,400
He Yiwei.

834
00:25:42,580 --> 00:25:43,660
(That's me)

835
00:25:43,680 --> 00:25:44,560
It's him.

836
00:25:44,560 --> 00:25:45,240
It's this guy.

837
00:25:45,240 --> 00:25:45,840
Tell me.

838
00:25:46,440 --> 00:25:47,760
How am I worse than him?

839
00:25:48,560 --> 00:25:51,020
You're worse than him in every way.

840
00:25:51,020 --> 00:25:54,140
(Reputation-wise)

841
00:25:54,320 --> 00:25:54,880
Guys,

842
00:25:54,880 --> 00:25:55,820
too blunt.

843
00:25:55,820 --> 00:25:56,700
(Tone it down)

844
00:25:56,720 --> 00:25:57,960
Come here. Let's compare.

845
00:25:57,960 --> 00:25:58,880
(Give him a fair shot)
Stand here.

846
00:25:58,880 --> 00:25:59,240
Let's compare.

847
00:25:59,640 --> 00:26:01,200
It's okay.

848
00:26:01,200 --> 00:26:02,320
(Backing his bro up)
Let's see. Come on.

849
00:26:04,400 --> 00:26:05,480
Is it looks?

850
00:26:06,600 --> 00:26:07,560
Or height?

851
00:26:08,940 --> 00:26:10,740
(Comparison steals joy)

852
00:26:11,040 --> 00:26:13,600
Honestly, they're pretty evenly matched.

853
00:26:13,600 --> 00:26:15,080
(I won't say anything hurtful)
Very close.

854
00:26:15,080 --> 00:26:15,880
Hard to choose.

855
00:26:16,720 --> 00:26:17,580
Say something.

856
00:26:17,580 --> 00:26:18,780
(Desperately needs Jin's approval)

857
00:26:20,060 --> 00:26:21,740
(Choosing silence)

858
00:26:21,820 --> 00:26:23,380
(Exits in defeat)

859
00:26:23,400 --> 00:26:25,660
You dumped me for him?

860
00:26:25,660 --> 00:26:26,640
(Found a new barista)
Yep.

861
00:26:26,640 --> 00:26:27,480
Was it worth it?

862
00:26:28,560 --> 00:26:29,360
Pretty worth it.

863
00:26:29,360 --> 00:26:30,320
(Total win)

864
00:26:30,320 --> 00:26:31,580
I think I won here.

865
00:26:31,700 --> 00:26:32,820
(She's won over)

866
00:26:33,560 --> 00:26:34,680
Don't think

867
00:26:34,680 --> 00:26:35,880
I don't know

868
00:26:35,880 --> 00:26:36,760
your secret.

869
00:26:37,520 --> 00:26:38,320
What secret?

870
00:26:40,360 --> 00:26:41,960
Handsome Guys Cafe

871
00:26:41,960 --> 00:26:44,360
is clean inside and out.

872
00:26:44,520 --> 00:26:45,680
But you guys?

873
00:26:47,720 --> 00:26:48,880
That's hard to say.

874
00:26:48,880 --> 00:26:49,620
Hard to say?

875
00:26:49,620 --> 00:26:51,660
(What secret does
Liu Lian Wangfan know?)

876
00:26:51,960 --> 00:26:54,240
You run some VIP service.

877
00:26:54,240 --> 00:26:55,560
That's unfair competition!

878
00:26:56,120 --> 00:26:56,720
Exactly.

879
00:26:57,180 --> 00:26:58,540
(We're outworking you)

880
00:26:58,560 --> 00:26:59,480
Jin Cardashian.

881
00:26:59,480 --> 00:27:00,200
What?

882
00:27:00,200 --> 00:27:00,880
Come here.

883
00:27:01,320 --> 00:27:01,980
What's that supposed to mean?

884
00:27:01,980 --> 00:27:03,460
(Openly stealing a customer)

885
00:27:03,680 --> 00:27:04,680
Take a break.

886
00:27:04,680 --> 00:27:05,040
Sure.

887
00:27:05,040 --> 00:27:06,040
I'll go over for a bit.

888
00:27:06,040 --> 00:27:07,800
Don't worry. I'll be right back.

889
00:27:09,920 --> 00:27:11,240
This is

890
00:27:11,240 --> 00:27:13,040
the key to Manager Tui's office.

891
00:27:17,060 --> 00:27:19,060
(Manager Tui's office)

892
00:27:19,240 --> 00:27:20,720
He never lets outsiders in.

893
00:27:20,720 --> 00:27:22,480
(What's hidden in Manager Tui's office?)
No wonder he keeps staff out.

894
00:27:24,040 --> 00:27:25,240
Here's the key.

895
00:27:25,240 --> 00:27:25,680
Okay.

896
00:27:25,680 --> 00:27:27,120
See what

897
00:27:27,120 --> 00:27:28,680
shady stuff he's been doing in there.

898
00:27:31,280 --> 00:27:32,800
Guys, let's go!

899
00:27:33,400 --> 00:27:35,200
How do you have our boss' key?

900
00:27:35,800 --> 00:27:36,240
Yeah.

901
00:27:37,400 --> 00:27:38,160
How does he have it?

902
00:27:38,900 --> 00:27:41,180
(What's his history with Manager Tui?)

903
00:27:41,200 --> 00:27:41,840
Lets's grab some food.

904
00:27:43,320 --> 00:27:44,480
Food?

905
00:27:44,480 --> 00:27:45,640
Old man.

906
00:27:45,640 --> 00:27:46,720
(Unlock the detective team's
best moments early)

907
00:27:46,720 --> 00:27:47,720
Let's grab our snacks.

908
00:27:47,720 --> 00:27:48,200
(At every Tuesday noon,
Dungeon Unlocking)

909
00:27:48,200 --> 00:27:48,580
Really?

910
00:27:49,500 --> 00:27:50,940
(We'll need energy later)

911
00:27:50,960 --> 00:27:52,480
Here, try this. It's really good.

912
00:27:52,480 --> 00:27:53,280
(Snack delivery +1)
It's good.

913
00:27:53,280 --> 00:27:53,560
Alright,

914
00:27:53,560 --> 00:27:54,880
let's refuel for now.

915
00:27:54,880 --> 00:27:56,480
Next, we're heading to

916
00:27:56,480 --> 00:27:57,280
the boss' office

917
00:27:57,280 --> 00:27:59,200
to see what he's really up to.

918
00:27:59,760 --> 00:28:01,120
Can we take this to the boss' office?

919
00:28:01,120 --> 00:28:01,880
We can.

920
00:28:01,880 --> 00:28:02,520
Hold on to it.

921
00:28:02,520 --> 00:28:03,480
You might get scared and drop it later.

922
00:28:05,440 --> 00:28:06,440
Watch your back.

923
00:28:06,440 --> 00:28:07,860
Now I can scare people too.

924
00:28:08,060 --> 00:28:08,820
(The dragon slayer became the dragon)

925
00:28:08,840 --> 00:28:10,960
Let's see how long you can act tough.

926
00:28:10,960 --> 00:28:12,040
You've picked up bad habits now.

927
00:28:12,040 --> 00:28:13,120
Now we've got someone

928
00:28:13,120 --> 00:28:14,800
who looks even more scared than you.

929
00:28:14,800 --> 00:28:16,800
But once the lights go out,

930
00:28:16,800 --> 00:28:18,360
she'll still be the one protecting you.

931
00:28:18,640 --> 00:28:20,400
(Once it's dark, she shows herself)
Bam, bam. Two kicks.

932
00:28:20,400 --> 00:28:20,840
Ding.

933
00:28:20,840 --> 00:28:21,680
Ding Pudding.

934
00:28:22,100 --> 00:28:23,100
(Detective, come here)

935
00:28:23,120 --> 00:28:23,560
What?

936
00:28:24,840 --> 00:28:25,520
I love you so much.

937
00:28:27,780 --> 00:28:28,150
(Ding Pudding +100 stamina)

938
00:28:28,150 --> 00:28:28,700
(Source: random stamina points
spawn in the dungeon)

939
00:28:28,700 --> 00:28:29,260
(Use: stamina can be traded
for food supplies)

940
00:28:30,120 --> 00:28:31,760
What do you mean by that?

941
00:28:31,760 --> 00:28:32,560
What do you mean?

942
00:28:32,560 --> 00:28:33,200
We're good comrades.

943
00:28:33,200 --> 00:28:33,800
Good bros.

944
00:28:33,820 --> 00:28:35,820
(Me and my Detective bro)

945
00:28:35,840 --> 00:28:36,320
It's fine.

946
00:28:36,320 --> 00:28:37,280
I'll take it easy today.

947
00:28:37,280 --> 00:28:37,840
I won't grind then.

948
00:28:37,840 --> 00:28:39,600
(Truth Supply Station drops randomly)
We'll guilt-trip them later.

949
00:28:39,600 --> 00:28:40,600
(Everyone's food-and-chat mode
coming soon)

950
00:28:40,600 --> 00:28:41,560
(Eat them broke)
I don't think they'll let us

951
00:28:41,960 --> 00:28:42,840
(Who's trapping who?)
trap them.

952
00:28:42,840 --> 00:28:43,760
We can.

953
00:28:43,760 --> 00:28:44,680
Just act cute and whine a little.

954
00:28:45,160 --> 00:28:45,400
How?

955
00:28:45,400 --> 00:28:46,800
Beg me.

956
00:28:46,800 --> 00:28:47,640
Please, Ding.

957
00:28:48,960 --> 00:28:49,840
What the heck?

958
00:28:49,840 --> 00:28:50,720
Take it away!

959
00:28:51,920 --> 00:28:53,000
The boss' office.

960
00:28:53,720 --> 00:28:54,160
I'll do it.

961
00:29:04,040 --> 00:29:06,080
Starlight Cafe owner.

962
00:29:08,120 --> 00:29:08,560
Boss.

963
00:29:11,560 --> 00:29:13,040
Come on. Let Ding and

964
00:29:13,040 --> 00:29:14,320
Qian Jinding go first.

965
00:29:14,720 --> 00:29:15,200
I'll go first.

966
00:29:16,080 --> 00:29:16,880
(The scaredy-cat gets bold)
What's there to be scared of?

967
00:29:16,880 --> 00:29:17,480
Let's go!

968
00:29:20,340 --> 00:29:21,460
(No entry)

969
00:29:21,480 --> 00:29:22,000
It won't open.

970
00:29:22,520 --> 00:29:23,480
It really won't open.

971
00:29:25,480 --> 00:29:27,000
What does verification area mean?

972
00:29:27,920 --> 00:29:28,580
Verification area?

973
00:29:28,580 --> 00:29:30,300
(Verification area)

974
00:29:30,920 --> 00:29:31,600
Verification area.

975
00:29:34,760 --> 00:29:35,640
Facial recognition.

976
00:29:35,640 --> 00:29:36,360
Face?

977
00:29:37,220 --> 00:29:38,980
(Recognition failed)

978
00:29:39,280 --> 00:29:40,440
Only the boss can get in.

979
00:29:40,540 --> 00:29:41,720
(Guess: entry is boss only)

980
00:29:41,720 --> 00:29:42,920
We need to carry the boss over.

981
00:29:43,360 --> 00:29:45,000
Manager's abnormal heartbeat detected.

982
00:29:45,960 --> 00:29:48,100
Office security system
activated automatically.

983
00:29:48,180 --> 00:29:55,820
(Professional props. Don't try this)

984
00:29:55,840 --> 00:29:56,920
No, this is real...

985
00:29:57,960 --> 00:29:58,600
Help!

986
00:30:02,260 --> 00:30:06,060
(Security system activated)

987
00:30:06,540 --> 00:30:07,540
(Confused but still chewing)

988
00:30:07,560 --> 00:30:08,360
Hold on!

989
00:30:08,360 --> 00:30:09,160
I can't breathe!

990
00:30:10,280 --> 00:30:11,740
No, this is real!

991
00:30:11,740 --> 00:30:12,380
(Calm)

992
00:30:13,060 --> 00:30:13,880
(Worried about the strawberry)

993
00:30:13,880 --> 00:30:14,440
Hold on!

994
00:30:14,440 --> 00:30:15,200
My strawberry!

995
00:30:15,920 --> 00:30:17,390
(Worried about the strawberry +1)
My strawberry got smashed!

996
00:30:19,500 --> 00:30:20,900
(Trying to force their way out)

997
00:30:20,920 --> 00:30:21,800
Get out, quick!

998
00:30:21,800 --> 00:30:22,040
No.

999
00:30:22,520 --> 00:30:23,920
Someone has to hold it.

1000
00:30:23,920 --> 00:30:24,200
Come on.

1001
00:30:24,560 --> 00:30:25,360
I'll help you.

1002
00:30:25,360 --> 00:30:26,200
No, push it!

1003
00:30:26,200 --> 00:30:27,620
(Pushing together)

1004
00:30:27,620 --> 00:30:28,360
(Failed)

1005
00:30:28,360 --> 00:30:29,240
It's too tight!

1006
00:30:29,240 --> 00:30:30,600
Let's push it!

1007
00:30:31,080 --> 00:30:31,880
(Pushing hard)
Push harder!

1008
00:30:31,880 --> 00:30:35,020
(Pushing hard)

1009
00:30:37,860 --> 00:30:39,060
(Ah!)

1010
00:30:39,080 --> 00:30:39,720
Can you get out?

1011
00:30:40,040 --> 00:30:40,600
Can you get out?

1012
00:30:41,320 --> 00:30:42,120
Yes.

1013
00:30:42,120 --> 00:30:42,720
Quick.

1014
00:30:42,720 --> 00:30:43,800
Go outside.

1015
00:30:43,800 --> 00:30:44,800
It's still squeezing.

1016
00:30:44,800 --> 00:30:45,640
It's still squeezing me.

1017
00:30:46,340 --> 00:30:47,740
(Escaped safely)

1018
00:30:49,380 --> 00:30:51,260
(Rescue them fast)

1019
00:30:52,960 --> 00:30:53,840
Come on.

1020
00:30:54,360 --> 00:30:55,120
How do I get out?

1021
00:30:55,120 --> 00:30:55,960
I can't!

1022
00:30:55,960 --> 00:30:56,840
I can't get out!

1023
00:30:56,840 --> 00:30:57,640
Get out, quick!

1024
00:30:58,480 --> 00:30:59,480
No, this thing is really...

1025
00:30:59,480 --> 00:30:59,920
I can't get out!

1026
00:31:00,440 --> 00:31:02,440
Why does it feel like
it's getting smaller?

1027
00:31:04,100 --> 00:31:06,260
(The space inside is still shrinking)

1028
00:31:06,840 --> 00:31:07,240
It's too tight!

1029
00:31:07,240 --> 00:31:08,400
(Using all his strength)

1030
00:31:08,400 --> 00:31:09,480
I'm pulling!

1031
00:31:09,480 --> 00:31:10,560
You guys pull this side.

1032
00:31:10,560 --> 00:31:11,240
Okay, I'll pull here.

1033
00:31:13,880 --> 00:31:15,120
Let's push it.

1034
00:31:15,880 --> 00:31:16,800
I'll hold it.

1035
00:31:22,700 --> 00:31:23,980
(Willing to be the human shield)

1036
00:31:24,000 --> 00:31:24,200
Come on!

1037
00:31:27,280 --> 00:31:28,120
Go!

1038
00:31:28,120 --> 00:31:28,560
Jin, go!

1039
00:31:29,520 --> 00:31:29,920
Jin, go!

1040
00:31:34,320 --> 00:31:34,800
Hold on.

1041
00:31:34,800 --> 00:31:35,840
Brace it with your foot.

1042
00:31:35,840 --> 00:31:36,240
Okay.

1043
00:31:36,720 --> 00:31:37,640
You get out.

1044
00:31:37,640 --> 00:31:38,300
You get out. I'll do it.

1045
00:31:38,300 --> 00:31:39,940
(All four escape)

1046
00:31:40,080 --> 00:31:40,840
Hold on, Ning!

1047
00:31:41,440 --> 00:31:42,000
Are you okay?

1048
00:31:42,000 --> 00:31:42,840
I really can't get through.

1049
00:31:48,720 --> 00:31:49,420
I'll hold it for a bit.

1050
00:31:49,500 --> 00:31:51,060
( Ding willingly holds
the door for his Ning)

1051
00:31:51,520 --> 00:31:52,760
Pull again!

1052
00:31:53,760 --> 00:31:54,680
Ning, are you out?

1053
00:31:54,680 --> 00:31:55,800
Almost.

1054
00:31:57,180 --> 00:31:57,940
(Ah!)

1055
00:31:58,180 --> 00:31:58,660
(Ugh!)

1056
00:31:58,680 --> 00:31:59,280
Come out.

1057
00:31:59,280 --> 00:32:00,040
(Ah!)

1058
00:32:00,040 --> 00:32:00,600
Ding, get out.

1059
00:32:04,440 --> 00:32:05,520
Come out.

1060
00:32:06,980 --> 00:32:08,780
(Everyone escaped)

1061
00:32:09,400 --> 00:32:10,720
That was so scary.

1062
00:32:13,680 --> 00:32:14,520
What does that mean?

1063
00:32:14,520 --> 00:32:16,120
What does it mean?

1064
00:32:16,120 --> 00:32:17,080
What does this mean?

1065
00:32:19,520 --> 00:32:20,040
Safe.

1066
00:32:21,800 --> 00:32:22,200
Hold on.

1067
00:32:22,800 --> 00:32:23,440
It says

1068
00:32:24,160 --> 00:32:26,160
after the security system is activated,

1069
00:32:26,160 --> 00:32:28,040
visitors must pass
the verification system

1070
00:32:28,040 --> 00:32:28,800
to enter the office.

1071
00:32:28,800 --> 00:32:30,200
If there are multiple visitors,

1072
00:32:30,200 --> 00:32:32,480
everyone must verify together.

1073
00:32:32,480 --> 00:32:35,480
Everyone puts one finger
inside the red circle.

1074
00:32:35,480 --> 00:32:37,320
Each verification
has a one-minute limit.

1075
00:32:37,320 --> 00:32:38,440
If time runs out,

1076
00:32:38,440 --> 00:32:40,440
you must return
to the start and re-enter.

1077
00:32:40,440 --> 00:32:40,840
Right.

1078
00:32:40,840 --> 00:32:42,240
We need to go over together.

1079
00:32:42,240 --> 00:32:43,240
Everyone's finger

1080
00:32:43,240 --> 00:32:44,600
(Six fingerprints needed)
has to go in that circle.

1081
00:32:44,600 --> 00:32:45,000
Right.

1082
00:32:45,000 --> 00:32:45,880
So we need

1083
00:32:45,880 --> 00:32:47,480
to stand in a line

1084
00:32:47,480 --> 00:32:49,140
(Ning, Jin, He, Ding, Ke, Qian)
and still touch it at the same time?

1085
00:32:49,140 --> 00:32:51,620
(Just came out, then went back in)

1086
00:32:51,660 --> 00:32:54,980
(All six fingers go in at once)

1087
00:32:55,600 --> 00:32:56,000
What?

1088
00:32:56,000 --> 00:32:57,840
I don't get it.

1089
00:32:57,840 --> 00:32:59,920
Put one finger in the red circle
at the same time.

1090
00:33:00,400 --> 00:33:02,040
(One finger each)
At the same time.

1091
00:33:02,600 --> 00:33:03,600
What do you mean by at the same time?

1092
00:33:03,600 --> 00:33:04,920
Is "at the same time"
that hard to explain?

1093
00:33:05,360 --> 00:33:05,800
Same time.

1094
00:33:05,800 --> 00:33:06,160
Okay.

1095
00:33:06,920 --> 00:33:07,680
Yes, sir.

1096
00:33:09,160 --> 00:33:10,960
So if we all go in together,

1097
00:33:10,960 --> 00:33:11,880
we have to touch it together.

1098
00:33:11,880 --> 00:33:12,180
Right.

1099
00:33:12,420 --> 00:33:13,480
(Must enter the narrow space
within one minute)

1100
00:33:13,480 --> 00:33:14,480
(All six fingerprints must enter
the verification zone at once)

1101
00:33:14,480 --> 00:33:15,690
(Ning Bubble, Jin Cardashian, He Yiwei)

1102
00:33:15,690 --> 00:33:16,610
(Ding Pudding, Ke Coffee, Qian Jinding)

1103
00:33:16,640 --> 00:33:17,520
But we're chubby.

1104
00:33:17,520 --> 00:33:18,360
You guys are skinny.

1105
00:33:18,460 --> 00:33:19,080
(Different heights and builds)

1106
00:33:19,080 --> 00:33:20,040
Good question.

1107
00:33:20,040 --> 00:33:21,760
How do we all get over there?

1108
00:33:23,120 --> 00:33:24,440
I think the thinnest person

1109
00:33:24,440 --> 00:33:25,720
should stand at the end.

1110
00:33:25,720 --> 00:33:26,280
No.

1111
00:33:26,280 --> 00:33:27,600
The person with the longest arms
should be at the end.

1112
00:33:28,080 --> 00:33:29,120
(Plan: Longest arms on the outside)
Long arms.

1113
00:33:29,120 --> 00:33:29,640
Right.

1114
00:33:29,640 --> 00:33:30,400
